  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to send multiple messages by tapping Enter so that I can chat.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: User types text in chat and taps on Enter to send it. As a result:\r\n\r\n1. Text is sent\r\n2. Input field contains text \r\n3. Cursor is moved to the next line in the input field\r\n\r\nNote: this issue does not exists in iOS. It works fine in iOS: user taps on Return -> text is sent and input field is cleared\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nWhen user taps on enter -> text is sent and input field is cleared\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nWhen user taps on enter -> text is sent; input field is not cleared and contains sent text; cursor is on the next line\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nscreencast: https://www.screencast.com/t/FY5nmFdV9yQ\r\n- Open Status, login\r\n- Open Contacts and open any contact\r\n- type \"1\" and tap on enter \r\n- type \"2\" and tap on enter\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.3\r\n* Operating System: Android \r\n",
